<subSubSection id="F4DFB7CBB314DE7757D90F275A41FE09" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BC7AE440B314DE7757D90F275A41FE09" blockId="20.[151,1436,310,1127]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7757D90F275822FEEC" bold="true" box="[197,319,346,371]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Cuticle dark. Elytra brown with two pale vittae on disk: both central vittae are short, interrupted on apical and basal third, with slightly convex subparallel borders.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F4DFB7CBB314DE7757D90FDF5850FCF5" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="BC7AE440B314DE7757D90FDF5B9CFE25" blockId="20.[151,1436,310,1127]" box="[197,641,418,443]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7757D90FDF586EFE24" bold="true" box="[197,371,418,443]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7756650FDE5B1DFE24" box="[377,512,419,443]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Body length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="7B3D49A5B314DE7755120FDE5B61FE25" box="[526,636,418,443]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">
7 
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7755000FD95B37FE24" box="[540,554,420,443]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">–</emphasis>
10 mm
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC7AE440B314DE7757D90FBB5B77FDD5" blockId="20.[151,1436,310,1127]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7757D90FBB5B2EFE41" box="[197,563,454,479]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7757D90FBB58C6FE40" bold="true" box="[197,475,454,479]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Cuticle and pubescence.</emphasis>
Cuticle
</emphasis>
color dark; head with pale patch on frons (
<figureCitation id="24FEF8C5B314DE77530D0FBB5D7EFE41" box="[1041,1123,454,478]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[253,1361,199,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[234,1368,193,1875]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 17. Head cuticle color: 12. E. excavate; 13. E. semivittata, E. missionum; 14. E. clericalis, E. luteolineata; 15. E. bosqi; 16. E. leopardina, E. monachica, E. rutilifrons; 17. E. grammica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203652/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number id="0A0DF667B314DE7753590FBB5D7EFE41" box="[1093,1123,454,478]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
); elytra with two pale vittae on disk; both central vittae are short, interrupted on apical and basal third, slightly and subparallel convex borders (Fig. 
<number id="0A0DF667B314DE7757CA0C7359E8FDB9" box="[214,245,526,550]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" value="25.0">25</number>
). 
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7756100C73588DFDB9" box="[268,400,526,550]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Pubescence</emphasis>
dense (
<number id="0A0DF667B314DE7756F70C735B2FFDB9" box="[491,562,526,550]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" value="26.0" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="23.0">23–29</number>
setae by lineal mm), elytral pubescence coincident with cuticle color. Legs pale. Abdominal pubescence light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC7AE440B314DE7757D90C2B5A6DFD61" blockId="20.[151,1436,310,1127]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7757D90C2B5871FDF1" box="[197,364,598,623]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7757D90C2B583AFDF0" bold="true" box="[197,295,598,623]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Habitus.</emphasis>
Head
</emphasis>
<number id="0A0DF667B314DE7756680C2B588AFDF1" box="[372,407,598,622]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" value="0.8">0.8</number>
times as long as wide (L/A: 
<number id="0A0DF667B314DE7755FD0C2B5A31FDF1" box="[737,812,598,622]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" value="18.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="16.0">16–20</number>
); mandible strongly curved (
<figureCitation id="24FEF8C5B314DE77536D0C2B5DD8FDF1" box="[1137,1221,598,622]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 11" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1906,1929]" captionTargetBox="[330,1252,208,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[310,1274,195,1758]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 11. Epicauta lopardina, 6. Labial palpi with segment III strongly expanded from the basal third to the apex; 7. Maxillary palpi large (three times width) compressed dorso-ventrally, tapering to the base and expanding to apex. E. leopardina: 8. Prementum with central area having ample concavity; E. clericalis: 9. Prementum straight. Mandible dorsal views: E. leopardina: 10 (b, see arrow); E. clericalis 11 (b, see arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203651/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number id="0A0DF667B314DE7753BA0C2B5DD8FDF1" box="[1190,1221,598,622]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); antennae without sexual dimorphism. 
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7756600C0158F6FD0C" box="[380,491,636,659]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Pronotum</emphasis>
square, impressed at apical third in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE77530E0C065D78FD0C" box="[1042,1125,635,659]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Elytron</emphasis>
subequal in width throughout. 
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7757D50CDD59E3FD28" box="[201,254,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Legs</emphasis>
with adhesive setae of fore tarsal pads uniformly distributed, with distal region bilobed; medial and hind tarsal pads with two longitudinal rows of adhesive setae. 
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7754080CBE5A47FD44" box="[788,858,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">Claws</emphasis>
with dorsal blade curved from base to apex, ventral blade slightly curved, broader than dorsal blade near apical third.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC7AE440B314DE7757D90D775850FCF5" blockId="20.[151,1436,310,1127]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
Male genitalia. Spiculum gastrale with two marginal acuminate prominences, inner area bulged, not extending beyond the marginal spines; lateral face slightly bulged (Fig. 
<number id="0A0DF667B314DE77547F0D535A9EFCD9" box="[867,899,814,838]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" value="36.0">36</number>
). Median lobe rather long, dorsal-hook; 
<emphasis id="8EB13852B314DE7752470D4D5C81FCD8" box="[1371,1436,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">uncus</emphasis>
robust (
<figureCitation id="24FEF8C5B314DE7757F00D2F585DFCF5" box="[236,320,850,874]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 44" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[242,1345,220,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[225,1359,193,1957]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 44. Aedeagus, lateral view: 37. E. bosqi: (a) aedeagus, (dt) dorsal tooth, (h) hook; 38. Epicauta clericalis; 39. E. excavata; 40. E. grammica 41. E. leopardina; 42. E. luteolineata; 43. E. monachica; 44. E. semivittata." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203654/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number id="0A0DF667B314DE77563C0D2F585DFCF5" box="[288,320,850,874]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" value="44.0">44</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F4DFB7CBB314DE7757D90D0A5AE6FC10" box="[197,1019,886,911]" pageId="20" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
